import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import tensorflow as tf
import keras as Ke
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense , Activation #, Dropout
from keras.optimizers import SGD #stochastic gradient descent
from keras.utils import np_utils
import tensorflow as tf


from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

from sklearn import datasets 

# imporatmos dataset 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
sheet_url = 'https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1mzGDT4Cj_WxZyVEwOjvhc4mfnW8esWcB5Z54zTdLTgs/edit#gid=1043736311'
url_1 = sheet_url.replace('/edit#gid=', '/export?format=csv&gid=')

# dataset entero
dataset = pd.read_csv(url_1,decimal=',')

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# Seleccionar los primeros 972 datos de las columnas X1, X2 y Z es decir de la figura 
datos = dataset.iloc[:972, :3]

# Dividir los datos en un conjunto de aprendizaje (80%) y un conjunto de testeo (20%)
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(datos.drop('Z', axis=1), datos['Z'], train_size=0.8, test_size=0.2)

# Dividir el conjunto de aprendizaje en un conjunto de entrenamiento (80%) y un conjunto de validación (20%)
X_entrena, X_val, y_entrena, y_val = train_test_split(X_train, y_train, train_size=0.8, test_size=0.2)

# parametros del modelo
NB_CLASSES = 1
OPTIMIZER = SGD() 
N_HIDDEN_1 = 13
N_HIDDEN_2 = 10
VALIDATION_SPLIT = 0.2

#Agrego HL
model = Ke.models.Sequential()
#HL 1
model.add(Dense(N_HIDDEN_1, name='HIDDEN1'))
model.add(Activation('relu'))

#HL 2
model.add(Dense(N_HIDDEN_2, name='HIDDEN2' ))
model.add(Activation('relu'))

#OL
model.add(Dense(NB_CLASSES, name='OUTPUT', ))
model.add(Activation('sigmoid')) 


#Compilamos el modelo
model.compile(optimizer = OPTIMIZER, loss='mse', metrics='accuracy')



#entrenamos la red
history = model.fit(X_train_concat, y_train_concat, verbose = 1, validation_split=VALIDATION_SPLIT, epochs= 20000, batch_size = 300)

#graficamos
plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
plt.title('Model accuracy')
plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.legend(['Train', 'Test'], loc='upper left')
plt.show()

score = model.evaluate(X_test_concat, y_test_concat, verbose = 1)
print (score)

model.weights

from matplotlib import cm
from matplotlib.ticker import LinearLocator

aux = model.weights
M1  = aux[0]
b1  = np.matrix(aux[1])

M2 = np.matrix(aux[2])
b2 =np.matrix(aux[3])

M4 = np.matrix(aux[4])
b4 = np.matrix(aux[5])
#%%
import math 
def RELU(matriz):
    Nr,Nc= np.shape(matriz)
    out = matriz*0
    for j in range(Nr): 
        for k in range(Nc):
            out[j,k]=max(0,matriz[j,k])
    return(out)

def sigmoid(x):
  return 1 / (1 + math.exp(-x))

#%%
# Dominio
X = np.arange(-6,6,0.05)
Y = X

xx,yy= np.meshgrid(X,Y)

NrowD=len(X)*len(Y)

D=np.zeros(shape=(NrowD,2))

i = -1
for x in X:
    for y in Y:
        i+=1     
        D[i,0] =x
        D[i,1] =y


P1 = np.matmul(D,M1) +b1  
last = RELU(P1)

P2 = np.matmul(last,M2) +b2  
last = RELU(P2)


P4 = np.matmul(last,M4)     
last = np.array([sigmoid(x) for x in P4])


zz=xx*0
j = -1
for i in range(len(X)):
    for k in range(len(Y)):
        j+=1
        zz[i,k] = last[j]
 

#%%
fig, ax = plt.subplots(subplot_kw={"projection": "3d"})

surf = ax.plot_surface(xx, yy, zz, cmap=cm.coolwarm,
                       linewidth=0, antialiased=False)

# Customize the z axis.
ax.set_zlim(-1.01, 1.01)
ax.zaxis.set_major_locator(LinearLocator(5))
# A StrMethodFormatter is used automatically
ax.zaxis.set_major_formatter('{x:.02f}')

# Add a color bar which maps values to colors.
fig.colorbar(surf, shrink=0.5, aspect=5)

ax.view_init(90, 45)

plt.show()

excel = pd.DataFrame(aux).T
#pasamos al excel
    
M1 = pd.DataFrame(M1)
M1.to_excel('M1.xlsx')

b1 = pd.DataFrame(b1)
